    <title>Overheard at Forum: Andre Lawson, Admissions and Recruitment Coordinator at the University of Nevada-Reno</title>
    <link>https://www.collegeboard.org/membership/all-access/admissions/overheard-forum-andre-lawson-admissions-and-recruitment-coordinator</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-image field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; rel=&quot;&quot; resource=&quot;https://www.collegeboard.org/sites/default/files/styles/all_access_image_style/public/Andre%20Lawson_0.jpg?itok=jLm2Fkr7&quot;&gt;&lt;img typeof=&quot;foaf:Image&quot; src=&quot;https://www.collegeboard.org/sites/default/files/styles/all_access_image_style/public/Andre%20Lawson_0.jpg?itok=jLm2Fkr7&quot; alt=&quot;Andre Lawson, Admissions and Recruitment Coordinator at the University of Nevada-Reno&quot; title=&quot;Andre Lawson, Admissions and Recruitment Coordinator at the University of Nevada-Reno&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-author field-type-text field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Kate Levin, Associate Director, External Communications&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-newsletter-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/forum-2014&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;Forum 2014&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/taxonomy/term/616&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;Admissions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/higher-education&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;Higher Education&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/university-nevada-reno&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;University of Nevada-Reno&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why are you attending Forum this year?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is my first year attending Forum. I came mainly to network and to gain more knowledge about what’s going on in Higher Education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What sessions are you most looking forward to?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Breakfast. Just kidding! I’m really looking forward to “Boosting Success Among Young Men of Color” and “The Gender Gap in Higher Ed: Context, Causes, and Campus-Based Responses.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In high school I was that underrepresented kid. I went to a high school with a lot of other kids like me and no college recruiter ever visited us to tell us what our options were, or help us take the next step. I started my work in higher education because I wanted to give back; to give these kids a fair chance and make it equal on all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s one thing you’ve learned so far?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I just got here, actually. I was working this morning, doing an on-campus visit and meeting with 40 students. I’m looking forward to everything I will learn over the next few days!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How will you take what you’ve learned at Forum and use it in your daily work?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’m eager to learn things I can really apply to my daily work; knowledge and tactics I can use to help get more kids where they need to be in terms of college access and success. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span property=&quot;dc:title&quot; content=&quot;Overheard at Forum: Andre Lawson, Admissions and Recruitment Coordinator at the University of Nevada-Reno&quot; class=&quot;rdf-meta element-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</description>
     <pubDate>Mon, 27 Oct 2014 19:51:13 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>ahexter</dc:creator>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">8211 at https://www.collegeboard.org</guid>
